SUMMARY:Blackout Poetry
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Blackout Poetry highlights hidden meanings and the spaces that
  exist within the material around us. By training our poetic vision thats 
 often necessary in any art-making\, students will create their own blackou
 t poetry\, focusing on negative space and transforming the meaning of exis
 ting materials. Materials will include newspapers\, magazines\, books and 
 Sharpie markers. This workshop is inspired by Jun Kanekos Silence Before S
 ound exhibition. Ages 16  Beginner Level \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.
 gov/node/188451
