SUMMARY:Studio55: Kitchen Lithography and Monotype Printmaking
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:In this 4-week class students will experiment with 2 technique
 s of printmaking\, geli plate monoprinting techniques and Kitchen lithogra
 phy. We will explore a variety of techniques and ideas using geli-plates u
 sing stencils\, painting techniques and photo transfer to create monoprint
 s. Kitchen lithography is a fun way to experience traditional lithography 
 using items found around the house. Using aluminum foil\, a China-marker a
 nd Coca-Cola we will create unique printed images. No experience necessary
 . Wednesdays\, Aug 5  26  12:00  3:00 PM (4 classes) Ages 55  Beginner-Int
 ermediate Level \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/189186
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/189186
END:VEVENT
